<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1610,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicName authority="Lepesme &amp; Breuning, 1952" authorityName="Lepesme &amp; Breuning" authorityYear="1951" box="[151,664,1610,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Megobaralipton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,333,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Megobaralipton</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lepesme, P. &amp; Breuning, S." box="[343,664,1610,1637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="139 - 142" refId="ref5951" refString="Lepesme, P. &amp; Breuning, S. (1952) Note preliminaire sur la classification des coleopteres cerambycides. Transactions of the IXth International Congress of Entomology, 11, 139 - 142." type="journal article" year="1952">Lepesme &amp; Breuning, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, previously considered as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Audinet-Serville, 1832" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Megopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1234,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Megopis</emphasis>
Audinet-Serville, 1832
</taxonomicName>
, was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z." box="[393,567,1647,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="219 - 234" refId="ref5366" refString="Komiya, Z. (2002) A Synopsis of the Prionine Cerambycid of the Genus Megobaralipton, New Status (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae). (Revisional Studies of the Genus Megopis sensu Lameere, 1909 - 1). Elytra, 30 (1), 219 - 234., 23 figs." type="journal article" year="2002">Komiya (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, who considered it as a genus and this generic position was followed and confirmed later on by 
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A." box="[360,672,1683,1709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref5526" refString="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A. (2014) Supplement to the Genus Megobaralipton (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae) (Revisional Studies of the Genus Megopis sensu Lameere, 1909 - 13). Elytra, (New Series), 4 (2), 187 - 199, 25 figs." type="journal article" year="2014">Komiya &amp; Drumont (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1610,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepesme &amp; Breuning" authorityYear="1951" box="[199,381,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Megobaralipton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,381,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Megobaralipton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly characterized by an elongated cylindrical body, head with robust and developed mandibles in males, each mandible furnished with two internal tooth; pronotum strongly convex, with lateral margins indistinct, and widest at posterior half; elytra elongated and generally parallel-sided with rounded apex (furnished with small sutural projection), and with two internal carinae, which start from base or humerus and meet each other at about ¼ of the length of elytra before apex (the inner most often absent); and by legs slender in both sexes (
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z." box="[159,317,1899,1925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="219 - 234" refId="ref5366" refString="Komiya, Z. (2002) A Synopsis of the Prionine Cerambycid of the Genus Megobaralipton, New Status (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae). (Revisional Studies of the Genus Megopis sensu Lameere, 1909 - 1). Elytra, 30 (1), 219 - 234., 23 figs." type="journal article" year="2002">Komiya 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Drumont, A. &amp; Ivanov, S. &amp; Do, C." box="[328,573,1899,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="14 - 17" refId="ref4723" refString="Drumont, A., Ivanov, S. &amp; Do, C. (2018 b) First report of the occurrence of the genus Megobaralipton Lepesme &amp; Breuning, 1952 in Vietnam (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae, Aegosomatini). Lambillionea, 118 (1), 14 - 17., 4 figs." type="journal article" year="2018">
Drumont 
<emphasis box="[435,484,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus comprises seven species and five subspecies organized into three species groups: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ritsema" authorityYear="1881" box="[330,456,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloripes">
<emphasis box="[330,456,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">bicoloripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[470,587,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">lansbergei</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[642,784,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">mandibulare</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A." box="[798,1095,1935,1961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref5526" refString="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A. (2014) Supplement to the Genus Megobaralipton (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae) (Revisional Studies of the Genus Megopis sensu Lameere, 1909 - 13). Elytra, (New Series), 4 (2), 187 - 199, 25 figs." type="journal article" year="2014">Komiya &amp; Drumont 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1610,2034]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="377" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
The geographic range of this genus corresponds approximately to that of Sundaland and partly extends to southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[238,308,2007,2033]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[320,377,2007,2033]" name="Laos" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Laos</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[438,533,2007,2033]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A." box="[548,847,2007,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref5526" refString="Komiya, Z. &amp; Drumont, A. (2014) Supplement to the Genus Megobaralipton (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Prioninae) (Revisional Studies of the Genus Megopis sensu Lameere, 1909 - 13). Elytra, (New Series), 4 (2), 187 - 199, 25 figs." type="journal article" year="2014">Komiya &amp; Drumont 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Drumont, A. &amp; Gouverneur, X. &amp; Tavakilian, G. &amp; Collard, S." box="[859,1104,2007,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" pagination="40 - 64" refId="ref4666" refString="Drumont, A., Gouverneur, X., Tavakilian, G. &amp; Collard, S. (2018 a) Contribution a l'etude de la faune des Prioninae du Laos (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Les Cahiers Magellanes (New Series), 29, 40 - 64., 18 figs." type="journal article" year="2018">
Drumont 
<emphasis box="[968,1018,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">et al</emphasis>
. 2018a
</bibRefCitation>
, b). In this work, we confirm the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepesme &amp; Breuning" authorityYear="1951" box="[355,537,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Megobaralipton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[355,537,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Megobaralipton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[574,634,151,177]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">India</collectingCountry>
, based on a recent collection of the species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Komiya &amp; Makihara, 2001)" baseAuthorityName="Komiya &amp; Makihara" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Megobaralipton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalimantanum">
<emphasis box="[1131,1329,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">M. kalimantanum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Komiya, Z. &amp; Makihara, H." pageId="2" pageNumber="377" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref5584" refString="Komiya, Z. &amp; Makihara, H. (2001) Two New Species of the Genus Megopis (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) from Indonesia and Malaysia. Elytra, 29 (1), 33 - 40, 7 figs." type="journal article" year="2001">Komiya &amp; Makihara, 2001</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion box="[445,615,187,213]" country="India" name="Mizoram" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">Mizoram State</collectingRegion>
. This discovery in 
<collectingCountry box="[828,886,187,213]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="377">India</collectingCountry>
extends the geographic range of the genus to the western part of its distribution.
</paragraph>
